commitResults.messageBody:
Enrollment and TimeTable have been added.

SemesterYear and StudentSemester now have `hashCode` and `equals` methods.

`User` has been provisionally added, but will be removed in a future
commit.

Stubs have been added for the `declare` command.

commitResults.messageTitle: Implement `declare major` and stubs for `module` commands
commitResults.messageBody:
`declare major` has been implemented together with serialization of the
major.

Stubs for `module add`, `module remove` and `module list` have been
added. The module codes are syntatically validated to be alphanumeric, but are not
yet validated for existence in module database.

Serialization is changed slightly with addition of `activeStudent`
field.

Some reorganization of code is done, but this is restricted to reduce merge
conflicts with other PRs.

commitResults.messageTitle: Implement `module add, remove, list` and module code serialization
commitResults.messageBody:
`module add`, `module remove` and `module list` have been implemented.

Serialization of the module code list has also been implemented.

Tentatively, these commands save module codes to a separate field in
`planner.json`. Amendments will be made in future commits to save module
`Enrollment`s in `TimeTable`s stored by `Student`s in later commits.
This is partly to alleviate the problem of merge conflicts from other
PRs.

commitResults.messageTitle: Implement `student add, remove, active`
commitResults.messageBody:
`student add`, `student remove` and `student active` are now
implemented.

Currently, there must be at least one student in the student list.
Therefore, removing a student is forbidden if there is only one student.

Students can be added with their name and major:
`student add n/Alice major/CS`. Duplicate students are forbidden.

A student can be set as the active student with
`student active [INDEX]`, where `INDEX` is a one-based index.

Currently, students only store their name and major. This will be
changed in future commits which will store timetables and matriculation
requirements in `Student`.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add sample planner fallback, `student list`
commitResults.messageBody:
A valid sample planner is now used if the `planner.json` file cannot be
loaded or is invalid. This keeps the planner state valid.

`student list` which shows the list of students added is now implemented.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add serialization of `TimeTableMap` and related classes
commitResults.messageBody:
`TimeTableMap`, `StudentSemester` and `Enrollment` can now be
serialized and saved to file.

Each `Student` now stores a `TimeTableMap`, allowing switching between
timetables to be implemented.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix serialization of `TimeTableMap`
commitResults.messageBody:
`TimeTableMap` is now serialized correctly (including component classes
such as `Enrollment`)

commitResults.messageTitle: Implement `timetable active, list`
commitResults.messageBody:
Switching between timetables is now possible with `timetable active year/YEAR sem/SEM`.
A list of available years for the active student can be displayed with `timetable list`.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add `timetable add, remove`, checks to `module`
commitResults.messageBody:
Timetables can be added and removed with the
`timetable add/remove year/[YEAR] sem/[SEM]` sub-commands respectively.
Validation has also been added to `module` sub-commands to reject the
command if no student or timetable is active.

A known bug is that the timetables of a `Student` instance isn't saved
in the `students` list in JSON. This is due to `UniqueStudentList#get`
(implemented by `ObservableList<Student>`) returning a copy of the `Student` retrieved.
This will be fixed in a future commit.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add `student` and `timetable` commands to user guide
commitResults.messageBody:
The user guide now documents the sub-commands in the `student` and
`timetable` commands.

commitResults.messageTitle: Remove `PlannerModelManager`
commitResults.messageBody:
`PlannerModelManager` has been removed. Its methods have been moved to
`ModelManager`.

Fixed minor bug where the student name was used instead of the major name in
`Student#toString`.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor sample model methods into `SampleDataUtil`
commitResults.messageBody:
Sample data methods for `Planenr`, `TimeTable`, `TimeTableMap` and
`Student` are now in `SampleDataUtil`.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add `CumulativeGrade` and `student grade` command
commitResults.messageBody:
Logic has been added to accumulate and calculate the student's overall
grade.

The `student grade` command now displays the student's overall grade and
MCs taken. A further command to declare grades will be added in a later
commit.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add `module grade` command
commitResults.messageBody:
The `module grade` command can now be used to declare grades in the
enrolled modules contained in the active semester's timetable.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add display of individual module grades
commitResults.messageBody:
The grade of each module is now displayed with the `student grade` command.

Additionally, `module grade MODULE_CODE` now shows the grade of the module in the active semester's timetable.

commitResults.messageBody:
Use cases for students/plans, timetables and modules have been added to
the DG.

I have also added more links to refer the user to other parts of the UG.

commitResults.messageTitle: Reorder structure of UG
commitResults.messageBody:
This is due to a suggestion from the PE-D https://github.com/AY1920S2-CS2103T-W13-4/main/issues/174 .
Now Student Management is before Degree and Grade Management, which is
before Timetable and then Module management.

This lets the user read the UG from top to bottom (with the exception of
`module grade`, which has a link to the Module Management section).
